        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:16px !important">Nigeria eyes G20 and BRICS</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-4-1.jpg" alt="Nigeria eyes G20 and BRICS" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Nigeria has officially <a href="https://www.dw.com/en/nigeria-seeks-south-africas-help-to-join-g20-brics/a-70943063" target="_blank">requested</a> South Africa's endorsement to join the G20 and BRICS group of leading and emerging economies during the bi-annual talks in Cape Town. Nigerian Minister of State for Foreign Affairs, Bianca Odumegwu-Ojukwu, emphasized the significance of enhancing cooperation in strategic sectors like mining and infrastructure to leverage economic potential, as South Africa <a href="https://www.cnbcafrica.com/2024/south-africa-takes-g20-helm-as-polarisation-complicates-agenda/" target="_blank">assumed</a> the G20 presidency.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">South African Minister of International Relations Ronald Lamola responded positively, highlighting the shared heritage between the nations and the expectation for closer collaboration to improve living conditions. However, both nations have a <a href="https://www.theafricareport.com/323356/nigeria-south-africa-a-complex-relationship-at-a-crossroads/" target="_blank">complex relationship</a> regarding economic competition and the treatment of Nigerians in South Africa. As BRICS continues to expand to include more African nations, with Egypt and Ethiopia recently <a href="https://www.africanews.com/2024/01/02/brics-expansion-five-countries-join-ranks/" target="_blank">joining</a> the club, Nigeria’s bid could strengthen its international influence.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <!-- Content sections -->
    <mj-section css-class="mj_section" background-color="#ffffff">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">South Korean martial law</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopolitics.world/email/images/gp-dec-4-2.jpg" alt="South Korean martial law" href="https://www.geopolitics.world" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter: blur(5px);">South Korea faces significant political turmoil after President Yoon Suk Yeol <a href="https://edition.cnn.com/world/live-news/martial-law-south-korea-intl/index.html" target="_blank">declared martial law</a>, accusing the opposition of anti-state activities and ties to North Korea. The martial law decree, the first since 1980, bans political activities and parliamentary functions and allows warrantless arrests. In an emergency late-night session, all 190 lawmakers in the National Assembly unanimously voted to block the decree, and President Yoon said he would revoke the law after almost 6 hours of its declaration. Experts and opposition call for the <a href="https://news.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20241204050015" target="_blank">impeachment</a> of the president.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4; filter: blur(5px);">Even Yoon’s ruling People Power Party members criticized the move, calling for the decree to be rescinded. The opposition has called this illegal, violates the constitutional and other laws, and called it a coup d’état. While the nation calls for the president’s impeachment, the Chief of Staff Chung Jin-suk, National Advisor Shin Won-sik, and Presidential Chief of Staff for Policy Sung Tae-yoon, along with seven other senior aides have tendered their resignations.​</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-width="1px" border-style="solid" border-color="lightgrey" padding="10px 12px" />
